{
  "texts": [
    "Related WorkLarge Language Models Different from other ML models, large models are designed to scale with increasing amounts of training data and computation resources [53][54][55][56].",
    "There are mainly two types of large model designs for natural language [57].",
    "(i) Unidirectional language models (e.g., GPT-3 [1]) use a single direction of text (allowing for efficient parallelization on increased computation power), i.e., assigning a possibility to a token sequence x = (x 1,..., x n).",
    "For instance, if we break down the sequence from left to right, the model calculates P(x) = P(x 1) ×... × P(x n |x 1,..., x n-1).",
    "Thus, such models are good at predicting tokens following the input text (e.g., text generation tasks)."
  ]
}